Class Filopodyan_

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.cam.gurdon.Filopodyan_
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, org.scijava.command.Command, org.scijava.plugin.SciJavaPlugin

    public class Filopodyan_
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.scijava.command.Command
    An ImageJ PlugIn for filopodia dynamics analysis. For the accompanying manuscript, see: Urbancic, V., Butler, R., Richier, B., Peter, M., Mason, J., Holt, C. E., Gallop, J. L. 2017. Filopodyan: An Open-Source Pipeline For The Analysis Of Filopodia. DOI: 10.1083/jcb.201705113
    Author:
    Richard Butler

      • setImageVisible

        public void setImageVisible(boolean v)
        Sets visibility of the current image and runs Enhance Contrast if it is visible. Does nothing in batch mode.
        Parameters:
        v - true to show, false to hide

      • setImp

      • filopodia

        public void filopodia(boolean prev,
                      FilopodyanProcessor filoProcessor)
        Detects filopodia in the image.
        Parameters:
        prev - true to run a preview, mapping only the currently displayed frame, false to run on all frames and continue to filtering and tracking
        filoProcessor - the FilopodyanProcessor to use to generate the binary mask
        See Also:
        LoGProcessor, ALTProcessor, ProcessProcessor, Tipper

      • filtered

        public void filtered(java.util.ArrayList<java.util.ArrayList<FiloPod>> backPass)
        Called by FiloFilter when filters have been applied. Takes the filtered Filopart list and creates a TrackEditor.
        Parameters:
        backPass - The Filopart Collection for use in TrackEditor. This is a List of timepoints each having a List of FiloParts.
        See Also:
        FiloFilter, TrackEditor, Filopart

      • trackEdited

        Called by TrackEditor to output edited Tracks.

        See Also:
